er more information per sniff than most existing noses the sensors made by sticking fluorescent compounds onto a backbone of dna are easy and cheap to make and could help the devices become widely available recommended stories see more joshua cohen joshua cohen joshua cohen cohen believes democracy depends on public discussion watch kwami coleman kwami coleman kwami coleman music phd student kwami coleman is captivated by jazz as a scholar and artist watch rob reich rob reich rob reich reich challenges students to think critically about how they live watch gallery a student in a chemistry lab christina cooley in a chemistry lab contact us follow us on twitter make a gift to h&s copyright 1997 2012 stanford university all rights reserved
